","format-standard","hentry","category-sin-al-ithm","tag-forgetfulness","tag-hypocrisy-al-nifaq","tag-knowledge-al-ilm","tag-light-al-nur-noor","tag-manners-adab","tag-parables-amthal","tag-teaching-al-taleem","tag-virtue-al-fadail"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-8vh","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":27142,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/02\/05\/believers-not-seek-hardship\/","url_meta":{"origin":32691,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Trials: Believers do not seek unnecessary hardship","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 5, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Hudhayfah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIt is not befitting for a believer to humiliate himself.\u201d They said, \u201cHow does he humiliate himself?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cHe confronts a trial he cannot endure.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2254 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32023,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/14\/jihad-al-nafs\/","url_meta":{"origin":32691,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Nafs: Only the strong can defeat their lower-self","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 14, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe strong are not those who defeat people. Rather, the strong are those who defeat their own ego.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Ibn H\u0323ibba\u0304n 717 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Arna\u2019ut \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37597,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/12\/23\/imams-dua\/","url_meta":{"origin":32691,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Jama\u2019ah: Imams should supplicate for their congregants too","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 23, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Thawban reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe one who leads others in prayer should not supplicate only for himself to the exclusion of them. If he does so, he has betrayed them.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 357 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Al-Tirmidhi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4101,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/04\/wise-man-good-fool-desires\/","url_meta":{"origin":32691,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Wisdom: Wise man does good, fool seeks desires","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 4, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Shaddad ibn Aws reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe wise man is one who holds himself accountable and performs good deeds to prepare for what comes after death. The foolish man is one who gives into his lowly desires and seeks their indulgence from Allah.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17173,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/12\/13\/believers-put-to-trial-sins\/","url_meta":{"origin":32691,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Trials: Believers put to trial until all sins expiated","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 13, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe believing men and women continue to be under trial in their lives, their children, and their wealth, until they meet Allah without any sin.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2399 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Tirmidhi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":39789,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/04\/19\/conscience-admonish\/","url_meta":{"origin":32691,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Conscience: Allah makes his heart admonish him with good","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 19, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Umm Salamah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen Allah intends goodness for a servant, He appoints a conscience within him to command and prohibit him.\u201d Source: Zahr al-Firdaws 227 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to al-\u2018Iraqi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u062